title: For Sale:  Walther P99as
postcontent: Unfortunately, I need the money so I'm letting go of my near mint-condition Walther P99AS, w/ original case,mags, backstraps, paperwork. It's had under 200 rounds through it, but has been dead-nuts accurate, with 100% reliability. These are considered in some circles to be the finest polymer-framed 9mm duty pistol made. The slides are Tenifer treated for wear and corrosion resistence, and features a decocking button, which safely returns the pistol to double-action mode (much like the Sigs, Beretta 92, CZ75BD, etc.) , making it vastly safer to carry or store with a chambered round, while still retaining the ability to fire instantly without any traditional safety in the way (this pretty much negates the likelyhood of an accidental discharge, as has become so common with Glocks and other striker fired safetyless pistols.)These also have the Euroepean-style paddle-type ambidetrous magazine release, whcih make it nearly impossible to accidentally release a magazine, as can happen with the more common button releases. Another unique feature is that these have a "double strike" capability, meaning if you get a bad primer strike, you can immediately pull the trigger again, you don't have to pull the slide to eject the round and re-cycle the action, as with other striker-fired designs.This  was made in Ulm,Germany, like all the other "real" Walthers of the past 100 years, it isn't one of the SW99 collaborations with Smith & Wesson (not that there was anything wrong with them, that just matters to some folks).And yes, this was the James Bond gun during the Pierce Brosnan years !!Buyer must be a Georgia resident that is over 21 and otherwise legally allowed to own fireams,and have valid ID. I have my Georgia carry permit, so I'm good to go.Thanks for looking......P.S. The photo with the case and papers is of the actual pistol, the other one is just a pic I borrowed of the interwebz, but it had much better clarity, and is identical.
